body:
Can we refactor this block as follows? I understand the reasoning here, but having empty branches can be a bit confusing and mask the code's real intentions.
```suggestion
		if handler != nil {
			if r.omitRouteFromContext {
				// Only populate the match vars (if any) into the context.
				req = requestWithVars(req, match.Vars)
			} else {
				req = requestWithRouteAndVars(req, match.Route, match.Vars)
			}
		}
```

